default&#xa0;defaultFOILdefault (The Forum of Insurance Lawyers) exists to provide a forum for communication and the exchange of information between lawyers acting predominantly or exclusively for insurance clients (except legal expenses insurers) within firms of solicitors, as barriste
defaultrs, or as in-house lawyers for insurers or self-insurers. FOIL is an active lobbying organisation on matters concerning insurance litigation. 
default&#xa0;
defaultFOILdefault represents over 8
default000 members. It is the only organisation which represents solicitors who act for defendant
defaults in civil proceedings.
