defaultFurther reformsdefault&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is already recognised, by a ban on the practice by CMCs, that it is undesirable for potential claimants to be offered an
default immediate inducement to bring a claim. Inevitably some claimants will be encouraged to make a fraudulent claim by the promise of an immediate benefit, before they have had a chance to think through the consequences of such a step. FOIL believes that the b
defaultan should be extended to law firms to completely outlaw this practice. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWhen asked during the course of giving oral evidence to the Committee, what compensation would be appropriate for a whiplash injury, James Dalton
default from the ABI replied that it was “
defaultwhatever society determines is the right amount which will then be built into insurance premiums
default”. FOIL would suggest that, bearing in mind the heavy burden claims place on motorists and the current concerns ove
defaultr the high cost of living, 
defaultsociety may reasonably consider that the current level of compensation for whiplash claims is adequate. Without intervention the level of damages
default set out in the Judicial College
default Guidelines
default 
defaultwill contin
defaultu
defaulte to rise. 
defaultFOIL 
defaultwould sugges
defaultt that steps should be taken to ensure that, 
defaultfor a
default period, damages 
defaultin low value RTA claims 
defaultshould not rise further. 
default This is a matter which ultimately will need to be considered by the judiciary but FOIL would welcome the Committee’s examination of the iss
defaultue. 
